Knowing that species it's likely piercing.
The bill seems much longer than you'd expect with Woodnymphs ? so I guess most of the nonidentified birds are Woodnymphs as well.
The bird seems to have no tail.
The bird seems to have no tail.
difficult to say whether it is feeding or whether the bill is actually pointed upwardly somewhere behind the flower.
